001015>)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:9974:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001474> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002385>)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:10403:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001495> \"Note: in FMA isa muscle of pectoral girdle; todo - resolve spatial disjointness inconsistencies and add\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:12354:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001693> \"TODO - check FMA - currently we place this as both of a zone of bone organ and an (endochondral) bone. Removed endochondral bone classification for now, violates disjointness axiom\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:13598:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001801> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001802>)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:13768:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001839> \"Ideally we would place a spatially disjoint from relationship to membranous labyrinth, but there are many parts in common. this should be resolved.\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:14474:AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#source> \"ABA\"^^xsd:string) <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002028> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001891>)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:14480:AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#source> \"ABA\"^^xsd:string) <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002028> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001894>)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:15271:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002100> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0000033>)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:15276:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002100> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0000026>)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:15430:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002104> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002105>)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:15708:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002113> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0000160>)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:16382:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002205> \"not to be confused with manubrium of eardrum. todo - find reference to support disjointness assertion with teleost\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:16938:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002240> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0000955>)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:17075:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002268> \"note - fma general anatomical term. xao has no subtypes (but Johnstons organ develops from this). An olfactory organ overlaps with the olfactory system, because some parts of the nose (e.g. nasal skeleton) are parts of the skeletal system, which is spatially disjoint\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:17334:AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#source> \"ABA\"^^xsd:string) <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002298> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002037>)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:17338:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002298> \"ZFA includes the tegmentum, MA the whole midbrain. Both include medulla oblongata. Here we make an overlaps link between midbrain and brainstem. Note that ABA states that cerebellum and brainstem are spatially disjoint. We do NOT include this axiom here, as it leads to multiple inconsistencies. This needs addressed in more detail.\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:18052:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002364> \"most AOs consider this part of the middle ear, so we go with this and place it in the middle ear as a border to the external, although it could be considered to overlap the external ear in that it has an EAM layer as part - for this reason we do not consider middle and external ear to be spatially disjoint. Development notes: The tympanic membrane (TM) has three layers, two epithelia provided by the external acoustic meatus (EAM) and the MEC, derived respectively from the first pharyngeal cleft and pouch, and a mesenchymally derived fibrous stratum[PMID:11237469]\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:18485:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002385> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0003714>)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:21633:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0003128> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0001684>)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:23702:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0003461> \"AO notes: this is a forelimb bone in MA, but this would lead to part-disjointness violations. Subtypes are clavicle, scapula, humerus\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:26282:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0003703> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002107>)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:34036:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0004743> \"Procoracoid+coracoid are homologuous with coracoid of teleostomi. The coracoid is a triangular shaped-bone that usually has an anteriorly directed long process that may joins its counterpart in some fish groups. It may be perforated by the coracoid foramen or it may be notched dorsally and forms the scapulo-coracoid foramen together with a similar notch of the ventral margin of the scapula[VAO] Editor notes: we would like to make pectoral girdle and limb spatially disjoint, check where this structure belongs // check coracoid process // see also - procoracoid and epicoracoid\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:38482:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0006205> \"we include a disjointness axiom to avoid confusion that may arise from the synonyms 'ligamentum pectineale' and 'ligamentum pectinum'\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:39061:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0006292> \"Note that this is part of the forelimb skeleton in EHDAA2, but this violates part-disjointness\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:43068:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0007823> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0004708>)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:47957:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0010379> \"Editors note: declaring this to be both smooth muscle and part of the LPS leads to a disjointness violation (smooth muscle and striated muscle)\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:50485:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000062> \"disjoint_from part_of, but this cannot be expressed in OWL2\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:50932:Declaration(AnnotationProperty(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#disjointness_axiom_removed>))\nmusculoskeletal.owl:50933:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#disjointness_axiom_removed> \"A class which has a weakened disjointness axiom, to avoid inconsistency. These are kept separately in the uberon_disjoint_from_strict ontology.\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:50934:SubAnnotationPropertyOf(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#disjointness_axiom_removed> <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#SubsetProperty>)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:51001:Declaration(AnnotationProperty(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from>))\nmusculoskeletal.owl:51002:AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> \"SO:cjm\"^^xsd:string) <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> \"A is spatially_disjoint_from B if they have no parts in common.\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:51003:AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> \"shares_no_parts_with\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:51004:AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#id> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> \"spatially_disjoint_from\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:51005:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000425> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> \"Class: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Nothing> EquivalentTo: (BFO_0000050 some ?X) and (BFO_0000050 some ?Y)\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:51006:AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> \"non_overlapping_with\"^^xsd:string)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:51007:AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#is_metadata_tag> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> \"true\"^^xsd:boolean)\nmusculoskeletal.owl:51008:AnnotationAssertion(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#is_class_level> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/uberon#spatially_disjoint_from> \"tru