 UBERON:0002294 ! biliary system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:17097:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002330 ! exocrine system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:17098:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002390 ! hematopoietic system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:17099:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002405 ! immune system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:17100:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002416 ! integumental system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:17101:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002423 ! hepatobiliary system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:17102:disjoint_from: UBERON:0004456 ! entire sense organ system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:17112:comment: not to be confused with manubrium of eardrum. todo - find reference to support disjointness assertion with teleost\nmusculoskeletal.obo:17131:disjoint_from: UBERON:0006722 ! manubrium of malleus\nmusculoskeletal.obo:17740:property_value: \"spatially_disjoint_from\" UBERON:0000955\nmusculoskeletal.obo:17851:comment: note - fma general anatomical term. xao has no subtypes (but Johnstons organ develops from this). An olfactory organ overlaps with the olfactory system, because some parts of the nose (e.g. nasal skeleton) are parts of the skeletal system, which is spatially disjoint\nmusculoskeletal.obo:18052:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002330 ! exocrine system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:18053:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002390 ! hematopoietic system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:18054:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002405 ! immune system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:18055:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002416 ! integumental system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:18056:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002423 ! hepatobiliary system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:18057:disjoint_from: UBERON:0004456 ! entire sense organ system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:18112:comment: ZFA includes the tegmentum, MA the whole midbrain. Both include medulla oblongata. Here we make an overlaps link between midbrain and brainstem. Note that ABA states that cerebellum and brainstem are spatially disjoint. We do NOT include this axiom here, as it leads to multiple inconsistencies. This needs addressed in more detail.\nmusculoskeletal.obo:18132:property_value: \"spatially_disjoint_from\" UBERON:0002037\nmusculoskeletal.obo:18336:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002390 ! hematopoietic system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:18337:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002405 ! immune system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:18338:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002416 ! integumental system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:18339:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002423 ! hepatobiliary system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:18340:disjoint_from: UBERON:0004456 ! entire sense organ system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:18843:comment: most AOs consider this part of the middle ear, so we go with this and place it in the middle ear as a border to the external, although it could be considered to overlap the external ear in that it has an EAM layer as part - for this reason we do not consider middle and external ear to be spatially disjoint. Development notes: The tympanic membrane (TM) has three layers, two epithelia provided by the external acoustic meatus (EAM) and the MEC, derived respectively from the first pharyngeal cleft and pouch, and a mesenchymally derived fibrous stratum[PMID:11237469]\nmusculoskeletal.obo:19311:property_value: \"spatially_disjoint_from\" UBERON:0003714\nmusculoskeletal.obo:19314:disjoint_from: UBERON:0003714 ! neural tissue\nmusculoskeletal.obo:19498:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002405 ! immune system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:19499:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002416 ! integumental system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:19500:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002423 ! hepatobiliary system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:19501:disjoint_from: UBERON:0004456 ! entire sense organ system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:19798:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002416 ! integumental system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:19799:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002423 ! hepatobiliary system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:19800:disjoint_from: UBERON:0004456 ! entire sense organ system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:19999:disjoint_from: UBERON:0002423 ! hepatobiliary system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:20000:disjoint_from: UBERON:0004456 ! entire sense organ system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:20081:disjoint_from: UBERON:0004456 ! entire sense organ system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:20493:disjoint_from: UBERON:0005090 ! muscle structure\nmusculoskeletal.obo:21092:disjoint_from: UBERON:0010912 ! subdivision of skeleton\nmusculoskeletal.obo:22152:disjoint_from: UBERON:0003101 ! male organism\nmusculoskeletal.obo:22562:property_value: \"spatially_disjoint_from\" UBERON:0001684\nmusculoskeletal.obo:24766:comment: AO notes: this is a forelimb bone in MA, but this would lead to part-disjointness violations. Subtypes are clavicle, scapula, humerus\nmusculoskeletal.obo:27550:property_value: \"spatially_disjoint_from\" UBERON:0002107\nmusculoskeletal.obo:27574:disjoint_from: UBERON:0004755 ! skeletal tissue\nmusculoskeletal.obo:31463:disjoint_from: UBERON:0004770 ! articular system\nmusculoskeletal.obo:33673:disjoint_from: UBERON:0004772 ! eyelid tarsus\nmusculoskeletal.obo:36032:comment: Procoracoid+coracoid are homologuous with coracoid of teleostomi. The coracoid is a triangular shaped-bone that usually has an anteriorly directed long process that may joins its counterpart in some fish groups. It may be perforated by the coracoid foramen or it may be notched dorsally and forms the scapulo-coracoid foramen together with a similar notch of the ventral margin of the scapula[VAO] Editor notes: we would like to make pectoral girdle and limb spatially disjoint, check where this structure belongs // check coracoid process // see also - procoracoid and epicoracoid\nmusculoskeletal.obo:36050:disjoint_from: UBERON:0006633 ! coracoid process\nmusculoskeletal.obo:36294:disjoint_from: UBERON:0004764 ! intramembranous bone tissue\nmusculoskeletal.obo:37441:disjoint_from: UBERON:0009196 ! indifferent external genitalia\nmusculoskeletal.obo:39855:disjoint_from: UBERON:0005869 ! maxillary process of inferior nasal concha\nmusculoskeletal.obo:40340:disjoint_from: UBERON:0006205 ! pectineal ligament\nmusculoskeletal.obo:40895:comment: we include a disjointness axiom to avoid confusion that may arise from the synonyms 'ligamentum pectineale' and 'ligamentum pectinum'\nmusculoskeletal.obo:41520:comment: Note that this is part of the forelimb skeleton in EHDAA2, but this violates part-disjointness\nmusculoskeletal.obo:42764:disjoint_from: UBERON:0006713 ! foramen cecum of frontal bone\nmusculoskeletal.obo:45922:property_value: \"spatially_disjoint_from\" UBERON:0004708\nmusculoskeletal.obo:46108:disjoint_from: UBERON:0010372 ! uncinate process of ethmoid\nmusculoskeletal.obo:46109:disjoint_from: UBERON:0010373 ! uncinate process of pancreas\nmusculoskeletal.obo:48151:disjoint_from: UBERON:0008846 ! skeletal ligament\nmusculoskeletal.obo:49339:disjoint_from: UBERON:0010070 ! intermediate layer of tympanic membrane\nmusculoskeletal.obo:51257:disjoint_from: UBERON:0010373 ! uncinate process of pancreas\nmusculoskeletal.obo:51319:comment: Editors note: declaring this to be both smooth muscle and part of the LPS leads to a disjointness violation (smooth muscle and striated muscle)\nmusculoskeletal.obo:51544:disjoint_from: UBERON:0010912 ! subdivision of skeleton\nmusculoskeletal.obo:54510:comment: disjoint_from part_of, but this cannot be expressed in OWL2\nmusculoskeletal.obo:54562:id: spatially_disjoint_from\nmusculoskeletal.obo:54563:name: spatially_disjoint_from\nmusculoskeletal.obo:54565:def: \"A is spatially_disjoint_from B if they have no parts in common.\" [SO:cjm]\ndocs/combined_multispecies.md:203:* removing all disjointness axioms;\ndocs/odk-workflows/RepositoryFileStructure.md:30:| ncbitaxondisjoints | http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ncbitaxon/subsets/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl | slme |\ndocs/odk-workflows/RepositoryFileStructure.md:45:| disjoint_union_over.owl | None |\ndocs/resources/release-pipeline.graffle:1892:\\f0\\b\\fs24 \\cf0 external-disjoints.owl}</string>\ndocs/resources/release-pipeline.graffle:2442:\\f0\\b\\fs24 \\cf0 /taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl}</string>\ndocs/resources/release-pipeline.graffle:5345:\\f0\\b\\fs24 \\cf0 external-disjoints.owl}</string