e=\"lexical\"} ! anterior lateral line placode\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:197344:disjoint_from: UBERON:2001391 {source=\"lexical\"} ! anterior lateral line ganglion\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:197977:disjoint_from: UBERON:2001471 {source=\"lexical\"} ! posterior lateral line system\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:211702:disjoint_from: UBERON:3010380 ! outer fin tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:213846:disjoint_from: UBERON:4000122 ! acellular bone tissue\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:222837:relationship: mutually_spatially_disjoint_with UBERON:8440008 ! periventricular hypothalamic nucleus, intermediate part\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:222848:relationship: mutually_spatially_disjoint_with UBERON:8440007 ! periventricular hypothalamic nucleus, anterior part\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:222915:relationship: mutually_spatially_disjoint_with UBERON:0000956 ! cerebral cortex\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:222927:relationship: mutually_spatially_disjoint_with UBERON:0003881 ! CA1 field of hippocampus\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:223088:relationship: mutually_spatially_disjoint_with UBERON:8440033 ! infralimbic area\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:223101:relationship: mutually_spatially_disjoint_with UBERON:8440032 ! prelimbic area\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:226505:id: mutually_spatially_disjoint_with\nsrc/ontology/uberon-edit.obo:226506:name: mutually spatially disjoint with\nsrc/ontology/uberon-odk.yaml:79:    - id: ncbitaxondisjoints\nsrc/ontology/uberon-odk.yaml:80:      mirror_from: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ncbitaxon/subsets/taxslim-disjoint-over-in-taxon.owl\nsrc/ontology/uberon-odk.yaml:166:    - filename: disjoint_union_over.owl\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:12844:  ?x owl:disjointWith [\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:12864:# Annotation Property: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002171> (mutually spatially disjoint with)\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:12866:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002171> \"A is mutually_spatially_disjoint_with B if both A and B are classes, and there exists no p such that p is part_of some A and p is part_of some B.\")\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:12869:PREFIX mutually_spatially_disjoint_with: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002171>\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:12876:    owl:disjointWith [\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:12884:  ?x mutually_spatially_disjoint_with: ?y .\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:12886:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002171> \"mutually spatially disjoint with\"@en)\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:12888:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002171> \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/wiki/Part-disjointness-Design-Pattern\"^^xsd:anyURI)\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:14144:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002160> \"The original intent was to treat this as a macro that expands to 'in taxon' only ?Y - however, this is not necessary if we instead have supplemental axioms that state that each pair of sibling tax have a disjointness axiom using the 'in taxon' property - e.g.\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:14161:# Object Property: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002163> (spatially disjoint from)\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:14163:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002163> \"A is spatially_disjoint_from B if and only if they have no parts in common\")\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:14164:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002163> \"There are two ways to encode this as a shortcut relation. The other possibility to use an annotation assertion between two classes, and expand this to a disjointness axiom. \"@en)\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:14165:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000232> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002163> \"Note that it would be possible to use the relation to label the relationship between a near infinite number of structures - between the rings of saturn and my left earlobe. The intent is that this is used for parsiomoniously for disambiguation purposes - for example, between siblings in a jointly exhaustive pairwise disjointness hierarchy\")\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:14167:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002163> \"spatially disjoint from\")\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:14168:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:seeAlso <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002163> \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/wiki/Part-disjointness-Design-Pattern\"^^xsd:anyURI)\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:14587:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002295> \"This property and its subproperties are being used primarily for the definition of GO developmental processes. The property hierarchy mirrors the core GO hierarchy. In future we may be able to make do with a more minimal set of properties, but due to the way GO is currently structured we require highly specific relations to avoid incorrect entailments. To avoid this, the corresponding genus terms in GO should be declared mutually disjoint.\")\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:15054:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002418> \"We would like to make this disjoint with 'preceded by', but this is prohibited in OWL2\")\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:93998:AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0044848> \"Note that phases are is_a disjoint from other biological processes. happens_during relationships can operate between phases and other biological processes e.g. DNA replication happens_during S phase.\")\nsrc/ontology/imports/merged_import.owl:168618:AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000410> \"Hard to give a definition for. Intuitively a \\\"natural kind\\\" rather than a collection of any old things, which a class is able to be, formally. At the meta level, universals are defined as positives, are disjoint with their siblings, have single asserted parents.\"@en)\n","exit_code":2,"status":"failed"}}
