{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_43","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,200p' ISSUE_COMMENTS.md && sed -n '1,240p' PR_COMMENTS.md\"","aggregated_output":"Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n\nThe problematic GO disjointness frames have been removed from the OBO edit file and the equivalent axioms have been moved to the imported OWL component, following the approach suggested in the issue.\n## Summary\n\nMoved the two disjointness axioms involving `UBERON:0000001` and GO classes out of `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` and into `src/ontology/components/disjoint_union_over.owl`.\n\nThis addresses issue #3651 by avoiding bare GO term frames in the OBO edit file:\n\n- removed the `GO:0005623` frame containing only `disjoint_from: UBERON:0000001`\n- removed the `GO:0110165` frame containing only `disjoint_from: UBERON:0000001`\n- added equivalent OWL Functional Syntax `DisjointClasses` axioms to `disjoint_union_over.owl`\n\n## Rationale\n\nThe original OBO `disjoint_from` axioms can be serialized by OWLAPI-based tools onto GO term frames because class disjointness is symmetric and the serializer orders operands lexicographically. That creates unlabeled GO term frames in the OBO source, which is invalid from the OBO perspective.\n\nKeeping these axioms in the existing imported OWL component preserves the OWL semantics while avoiding the OBO serialization problem.\n\n## Checklist\n\n- Read imported issue title, body, and comments from `__issue_context__.json`.\n- Checked the existing `UBERON:0000001`, `GO:0005623`, and `GO:0110165` OBO stanzas with `obo-grep.pl`.\n- Confirmed `disjoint_union_over.owl` is already imported by the edit file and listed as a component product.\n- Removed the bare GO-only OBO frames.\n- Added equivalent OWL `DisjointClasses` axioms to `disjoint_union_over.owl`.\n- Reviewed the final diff to confirm the change is limited to the two ontology files.\n- Ran `git diff --check`.\n\n## Validation Notes\n\n`robot convert -i src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo -f obo -o src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` could not be run because `robot` is not installed in this evaluation environment (`robot: command not found`). `owltools` was also unavailable.\n\nAvailable validation was limited to `obo-grep.pl` checks and `git diff --check`.\n\n@dragon-ai-agent\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
